Q_DESC:
Given an array arr[0..n-1] of distinct elements and a range [low, high], find all numbers that are in range, but not in array. The missing elements should be printed in sorted order.

Examples:

Input: arr[] = {10, 12, 11, 15}, 
low = 10, hight = 15
Output: 13, 14

INPUT
First line contains the size of array
Second line contains elements of the array
Third line conains the value of low
Fourth line contains the value of the high
OUTPUT
The output prints missing elements
